   <concept id="i1114676"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">10.001</ph> Policy.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d626e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d640e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                   Agencies shall-</p>
               <ol id="d626e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d640e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         Ensure that
legitimate needs are identified and trade-offs evaluated to acquire
items that meet those needs;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d640e36" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         Conduct
market research appropriate to the circumstances-</p>
                     <ol id="d626e42" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e46" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Before developing
new requirements documents for an acquisition by that agency;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e55" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Before
soliciting offers for acquisitions with an estimated value in excess
of the simplified acquisition threshold;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e64" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Before
soliciting offers for acquisitions with an estimated value less
than the simplified acquisition threshold when adequate information
is not available and the circumstances justify its cost;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e73" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iv)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Before
soliciting offers for acquisitions that could lead to consolidation
or bundling (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C.644(e)(2)(A)</xref>) and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C. 657q</xref>);</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e88" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(v)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Before awarding
a task or delivery order under an indefinite-delivery/indefinite-quantity
(ID/IQ) contract (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.</i>, GWACs, MACs) for a noncommercial
item in excess of the simplified acquisition threshold (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">10 U. S.C. 2377(c)</xref>); and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e104" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(vi)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               On an
ongoing basis, take advantage (to the maximum extent practicable)
of commercially available market research methods in order to effectively
identify the capabilities of small businesses and new entrants into
Federal contracting that are available in the marketplace for meeting
the requirements of the agency in furtherance of-</p>
                           <ol id="d626e110" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d640e114" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                     A contingency
operation or defense against or <ph class="- topic/ph ">recovery
from cyber,</ph> nuclear, biological, chemical, or radiological
attack; and</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d640e126" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                     Disaster
relief to include debris removal, distribution of supplies, reconstruction,
and other disaster or emergency relief activities (See <xref href="FAR-i1090608.dita#i1090608"
                                          base="i1090608"
                                          outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                          class="- topic/xref ">26.205</xref>); and</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d640e142" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         Use the
results of market research to-</p>
                     <ol id="d626e145" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e152" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Determine
if sources capable of satisfying the agency’s requirements exist;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e161" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Determine
if commercial items or, to the extent commercial items suitable
to meet the agency’s needs are not available, nondevelopmental items
are available that-</p>
                           <ol id="d626e164" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d640e171" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                     Meet the agency’s requirements;</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d640e180" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                     Could be
modified to meet the agency’s requirements; or</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d640e189" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(C)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                     Could meet
the agency’s requirements if those requirements were modified to
a reasonable extent;</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e200" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Determine
the extent to which commercial items or nondevelopmental items could
be incorporated at the component level;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e209" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iv)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Determine
the practices of firms engaged in producing, distributing, and supporting
commercial items, such as type of contract, terms for warranties,
buyer financing, maintenance and packaging, and marking;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e218" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(v)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Ensure
maximum practicable use of recovered materials (see <xref href="FAR-i1094654.dita#i1094654"
                                    base="i1094654"
                                    outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">subpart  23.4</xref>) and
promote energy conservation and efficiency;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e231" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(vi)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Determine
whether consolidation is necessary and justified (see <xref href="FAR-CEHHJBCII0.dita#CEHHJBCII0"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">7.107-2</xref>) (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C. 657q</xref>);</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e246" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(vii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Determine
whether bundling is necessary and justified (see <xref href="FAR-CEHDAJDFG1.dita#CEHDAJDFG1"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">7.107-3</xref>) (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C.644(e)(2)(A)</xref>);
and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d640e261" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(viii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Assess
the availability of electronic and information technology that meets
all or part of the applicable accessibility standards issued by
the Architectural and Transportation Barriers Compliance Board at
36 CFR part 1194 (see <xref href="FAR-i1077004.dita#i1077004"
                                    base="i1077004"
                                    outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">subpart  39.2</xref>).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d640e277" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                   When conducting
market research, agencies should not request potential sources to
submit more than the minimum information necessary.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d640e286" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                   If an agency
contemplates consolidation or bundling, the agency-</p>
               <ol id="d626e289" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d640e296" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         When
performing market research, should consult with the agency small
business specialist and the local Small Business Administration
procurement center representative (PCR). If a PCR is not assigned,
see <xref href="FAR-i1101041.dita#i1101041"
                              base="i1101041"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.402</xref>(a); and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d640e308" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         Shall notify
any affected incumbent small business concerns of the Government's
intention to bundle the requirement and how small business concerns
may contact the appropriate Small Business Administration procurement
center representative (see <xref href="FAR-CEHIGFCDH3.dita#CEHIGFCDH3"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">7.107-5</xref>(a)).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d640e322" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                   See <xref href="FAR-i1114778.dita#i1114778"
                        base="i1114778"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">10.003</xref> for the requirement
for a prime contractor to perform market research in contracts in
excess of $5.5 million for the procurement of items other than commercial
items in accordance with section 826 of Public Law 110-181.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
